messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 8/1/03 8:40:57 PM Pacific Daylight Time,
abtleo@... writes:

> Plant zuchinni. I can grow it, and my definition of gardening looks a lot
> like poking halfheartedly at the ground with a shovel, tossing on some seed
> and covering the lot with straw.
>
> brenda
>

Thanx Brenda, I may have to try that. I am desparate to grow food, the seeds
just see me and decide their fate before I take them out of the package. Last
year I went to Walmart, who in our area, has a humongous plant center. They
were out of seeds!!! I was shocked and disappointed until Phil (DH)said yeah,
well the earth must have let Walmart know I was on my way, so they decided to
save the seelings before I got there. It was hard to pout while I was laughing
so hard.

Rhonda

messages.messageBody:
8/1/03 00:32:

> This may be the plant for me. I have a serious black thumb! It saddens me
> that no matter what I plant, or how much I "try" to help it grow, it
> inevitably
> croaks :-(. Maybe I should try cherry tomatoes, cuz I love 'em and maybe they
> will feel sorry enough for me, that they will actually take root.

Plant zuchinni. I can grow it, and my definition of gardening looks a lot
like poking halfheartedly at the ground with a shovel, tossing on some seed
and covering the lot with straw.

brenda
